info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued December 10 at 5:43AM PST until December 10 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Spokane
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Wintry mix of sleet, freezing, rain, and heavy wet snow. Additional snow accumulations up to one inch. Up to 0.02" ice accumulation from sleet and freezing rain. * WHERE...Leavenworth, Plain, Holden Village, Stehekin, and Stevens Pass. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning. * IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. For the latest travel information in Washington, go to https://wsdot.wa.gov/travel
